    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen credibility factors are assessed and meet or exceed required levels for MRL 3. The 'Use error' factor was documented as not-assessed on the basis that the automated workflow eliminates analyst error pathways; however, this reasoning was not formally encoded as 'not-applicable' and the factor has not been evaluated against MRL 3 requirements. The assessment team accepted the package on the strength of the twelve assessed factors and the validation evidence demonstrating NIH predictions within experimental uncertainty across all five operating points. The oversight regarding 'Use error' encoding is noted for resolution in the next assessment cycle.",
